Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%g}(grated).

Drain and rinse the @Mixed Beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Next, add the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%g} and @Caribbean Style Jerk{2%sachets}. Fry for ~{1%min}.

Stir in the mixed beans, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{0.5%tsp} and @Water{100%ml}(for the sauce). Bring to the boil, then lower to a simmer. Cook until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%mins}.

Meanwhile, halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a #board{}, face-down.

Slice into 1cm thick slices. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Remove from the heat, then stir in the @BBQ Sauce{48%g} and @Butter{20%g}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with your Caribbean style BBQ bacon and beans. Sprinkle over the Cheddar and @Crispy Onions{1%sachet}.

Finish by fanning out the sliced avocado on top of each bowl. Enjoy!